The paper presents a method for training complex world models using multiobjective optimization, which is a common technique in machine learning and optimization research (cs.LG). The method is specifically designed for 3D environments, which suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of evolutionary-based optimization approaches, which is a common topic in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
